Device-RAID-Poller

This module provides a generic method for polling RAID array status
for multiple systems and supports easy additions of new backends via
modules.

The currently supported systems are listed below.

    FreeBSD GEOM mirror
    FreeBSD GEOM RAID3
    FreeBSD GEOM RAID
    ZFS
    Linux mdadm
    Adaptec arcconf
	Avago tw_cli

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Device::RAID::Poller

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Device-RAID-Poller

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Device-RAID-Poller

    CPAN Ratings
        https://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Device-RAID-Poller

    Search CPAN
        https://metacpan.org/release/Device-RAID-Poller

    Github Repo
	    https://github.com/VVelox/Device-RAID-Poller/

